article.headline: Oregon St. 73, Fresno St. 65
article.story: CORVALLIS, Ore. -- Calvin Haynes tied a career high with 25 points to lead Oregon State to a 73-65 victory against Fresno State on Wednesday night. Lathan Wallace added 13 points and Omari Johnson and Seth Tarver 12 each for the Beavers (6-5), who became the 15th Division I team with 1,600 victories. Paul George had 15 points for Fresno State (6-7). Haynes scored 13 of Oregon State's first 14 points of the second half, helping the Beavers build an 18-point lead. Fresno State trailed by 11 at halftime and got no closer until George's basket with 1:31 remaining made it 72-63. Oregon State never trailed after scoring nine straight points -- all on 3-pointers -- to take an 11-4 lead.
